INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (366,1,'2011-02-17 11:21:43','2011-02-17 11:21:43','SUKRUPA educates and enables more than 200 children from the slums in and around R.T. Nagar, Bangalore, providing a safe, caring, and clean environment for the children to live and learn in while their parents work.\r\n<h1>Our Programs</h1>\r\nWe holistically nurture our children and provide:\r\n<ul class=\"lined\">\r\n	<li>Nutritious food each day</li>\r\n	<li>Academic instruction in day school and after school programs</li>\r\n	<li>Health care</li>\r\n	<li>Skills training</li>\r\n	<li>Opportunities to participate in sports and other recreational activities</li>\r\n	<li>Cultural opportunities and awareness</li>\r\n	<li>Training by professionals in dance, music and visual arts</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Residential Program</h3>\r\nThe SUKRUPA residential program runs a stable, full-time home for up to 10 children. In this loving family environment, children who are orphaned, have single parents or come from families in crisis receive affection, nutrition and guidance. They are provided schooling, education, health care and nutrition, discipline, and mentoring so that they develop as any other child would.\r\n<div class=\"subarea lhside\" style=\"width: 275px;\">\r\n<h2>Why It Matters</h2>\r\nChildren at SUKRUPA come from urban slum communities around Bangalore.\r\n\r\nMany of them come from families whose monthly income is less than Rs. 2,000, which is <strong>less than $50.00</strong>. This leads to a lack of basic needs – like education, health care, and nutrition – and often enters the children into a vicious cycle of child labor and life-long poverty.\r\n\r\nDeprivation, poverty, and emotional trauma are a norm, and some children go through severe turmoil and abuse at home and in their communities.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Sukrupa Education Center</h3>\r\nSUKRUPA Education Centre currently provides free schooling, nutritious food and basic health care to a population of over 400 children who